<subSubSection id="B7C8652BFFAB7A03FF18FD3CFB40A9B3" box="[199,1209,655,680]" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="FF6D36A0FFAB7A03FF18FD3CFB40A9B3" blockId="9.[151,1436,151,789]" box="[199,1209,655,680]" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">
<emphasis id="CDA6EAB2FFAB7A03FF18FD3CFEB7A9BC" bold="true" box="[199,334,655,680]" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name alludes to the finger-like extensions of the pygofer process.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B7C8652BFFAB7A03FF18FD07FAF8A801" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FF6D36A0FFAB7A03FF18FD07FAF8A801" blockId="9.[151,1436,151,789]" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">
<emphasis id="CDA6EAB2FFAB7A03FF18FD07FEC2A9D9" bold="true" box="[199,315,692,717]" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName id="38D24D23FFAB7A03FD87FD06FC7BA9D9" authority="Distant" authorityName="Distant" box="[600,898,692,717]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Jassus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="determinatus">
<emphasis id="CDA6EAB2FFAB7A03FD87FD06FCEAA9D8" box="[600,787,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">M. determinatus</emphasis>
(Distant)
</taxonomicName>
in aedeagal characters but differs in having a much narrower apophysis of the style. Both 
<taxonomicName id="38D24D23FFAB7A03FD5CFD6AFD04A9E4" box="[643,765,728,752]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mahellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cardoni">
<emphasis id="CDA6EAB2FFAB7A03FD5CFD6AFD04A9E4" box="[643,765,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">M. cardoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="38D24D23FFAB7A03FCECFD6AFC3CA9E4" box="[819,965,728,752]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mahellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ungulatus">
<emphasis id="CDA6EAB2FFAB7A03FCECFD6AFC3CA9E4" box="[819,965,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">M. ungulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a similar dorsal marginal sclerotized process which is mesally directed and acuminate distally, but differing in curvature (see 
<figureCitation id="67E92A25FFAB7A03FBACFD4FFB0DA801" box="[1139,1268,764,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 52" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1716,1739]" captionTargetBox="[168,1421,432,1697]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,419,1713]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 52. Speceis of Mahellus. 48. Chaetotaxy of forefemur of M. distanti; 49. Chaetotaxy of metabasitarsus and second tarsomete of M. distanti, ventral view; 50 – 52. Posterior portion of male pygofer of Mahellus, dorsal view showing dorsal marginal sclerotized process: 50. M. cardoni sp. nov.; 51. M. distanti; 52. M. ungulatus sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/569771/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Figs 50, 52</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
